comments: Cauley-Stein (GSW) briefly places a hand on the opposite side of Towns (MIN) body as both players remain stationary. The contact is deemed marginal and does not affect Towns' (MIN) FOM.
After absorbing the body contact, Robinson III (GSW) brings his right arm down and makes contact to Layman's (MIN) elbow during his driving shot attempt.
Towns (MIN) is in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Towns (MIN) makes incidental contact to Russell's (GSW) arm after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Following the rebound, Towns (MIN) reaches in and initiates contact to Russell's (GSW) arm that affects his FOM.
Okogie (MIN) reaches in and makes hand on ball contact with Paschall (GSW) when the ball is dislodged during the drive. The contact is deemed incidental.
Chriss (GSW) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Okogie's (MIN) path when the contact occurs.
Towns (MIN) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Russell (GSW) after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Towns (MIN) initiates marginal contact to Paschall (GSW) during the screen and the contact does not affect his ability to defend.
Paschall (GSW) maintains a legal guarding position during Covington's (MIN) jump shot attempt.
Burks (GSW) makes contact to Towns' (MIN) arm during the rebound that affects his FOM.
Covington (MIN) makes clean contact to the ball as he engages with Burks (GSW) and a held ball is called.
Russell (GSW) gathers the ball on his right foot and then takes a legal two steps prior to his jump shot attempt.
Russell (GSW) slightly extends his forearm into Graham's (MIN) front but the marginal contact does not affect his ability to defend.

Robinson III (GSW) goes to and not through Graham (MIN) when the contact occurs at the end of the drive. The slight arm extension by Robinson III (GSW) is caused by both player separating or "releasing". Graham's (MIN) reaction is not consistent with the level of contact.
RLS shows that during the rebound, Towns (MIN) briefly engages Cauley-Stein's (GSW).  The contact does not affect Cauley-Stein's (GSW) ability to get to the long rebound.
Wiggins (MIN) slightly extends his forearm into Burks (GSW) front but the contact is marginal and does not affect his ability to defend.
Cauley-Stein (GSW) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Okogie (MIN) cleanly steals the pass intended for Cauley-Stein (GSW).
Russell (GSW) swipes down and cleanly dislodges the ball from Okogie (MIN) during his driving shot attempt. The ball is deflected out of bounds off of Okogie's (MIN) leg.
Cauley-Stein (GSW) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Okogie's (MIN) path when the contact occurs.
Covington (MIN) and Russell (GSW) briefly engage and separate during the loose ball.
Burks (GSW) places a hand on the opposite side of Towns (MIN) body but he immediately slides his hand off. The contact is deemed marginal.
Russell (GSW) briefly grasps Graham's (MIN) shorts during the rebound. The contact is deemed marginal.

Lee (GSW) delivers contact to Okogie (MIN) that affects his ability to maintain a legal guarding position. Lee (GSW) is not in Okogie's (MIN) view and does not give him room to avoid the contact on the back screen.
Lee (GSW) makes contact to Covington's (MIN) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Okogie (MIN) commits a take foul on Russell (GSW). Replay review of the foul called on Okogie (MIN) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.

Okogie (MIN) places a hand on Russell's (GSW) body but he immediately removes his hand as Russell (GSW) begins the upward shooting motion on his jump shot attempt. Russell's (GSW) reaction is not consistent with the level of contact.
